```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace(" ", "_") |> replace("-", "_")
end
```

This function takes a `String` as input and returns another `String` with the specified transformations applied. It first lowers the case of the string using `lowercase()`, strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip()`, and then replaces both spaces (`" "`) and hyphens (`"-"`) with underscores (`"_"`) using `replace()`.
